                   yields an estimate of the distance to the Galactic
                   center of R 0 = 8.3 $\pm$ 0.46 (statistical) $\pm$1.0
                   (systematic) kpc by simple geometry. Combining the
                   parallax and proper motion measurements for W51, we
                   obtained the full-space motion of this massive
                   star-forming region. We find W51 is in a nearly
                   circular orbit about the Galactic center. The H2O
                   masers used for our parallax measurements trace four
                   powerful bipolar outflows within a 0.4 pc size
                   region, some of which are associated with dusty
                   molecular hot cores and/or hyper- or ultra-compact H
                   II regions.},
